== English ==
=== Etymology ===
First coined by [[w:Alfred Kinsey|Alfred Kinsey]] of the [[w:Kinsey Institute|Kinsey Institute]], and later employed by [[w:Masters and Johnson|Masters and Johnson]] and the 1970 [[w:U.S. Census|U.S. Census]] forms.  
=== Pronunciation ===
* /moh·tohs/
=== {{initialism}} ===
# member(s) of the opposite sex
#:'''Usage note:'''  Sometimes used jokingly in the [[GLBT]] community as part of the greeting "Hello MOTOS!", a parody of a "Hello Moto!" advertising campaign run by [[w:Motorola|Motorola]].
